HOUSE RESOLUTION 239
By Lamberth
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Ann Sanders "Sandy"
Dickey on the occasion of her retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this legislative body should honor
those citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts and steadfast commitment to service,
have distinguished themselves in their professions; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Ann Sanders "Sandy" Dickey, who took a
well-earned retirement on October 1, 2025, following an exceptional thirty-eight-year career with
FedEx, where she served with dedication, leadership, and passion; and
WHEREAS, a native of Jackson and the daughter of Charles E. Dickey, Sr., and Virginia
McDade Dickey, Sandy Dickey graduated from Jackson High School and received her
bachelor's degree from the University of Tennessee, Knoxville; and
WHEREAS, after graduating from college, Ms. Dickey moved to Washington, D.C.,
where she worked on Capitol Hill for U.S. Senators David Pryor and Fritz Hollings; she later
worked for the U.S. Chamber of Commerce, where she lobbied members of Congress; and
WHEREAS, in 1987, she joined FedEx at the behest of the company's founder,
Frederick W. Smith, representing FedEx on Capitol Hill and establishing and overseeing its
state government affairs department; and
WHEREAS, Sandy Dickey was a lynchpin for the passage of multiple strategic federal
and state legislation critical to FedEx's operations; and
WHEREAS, a trusted and respected professional, Ms. Dickey was a five-time recipient
of FedEx's highest honor, the Corporate Five Star Award; and
HR0239
018383
- 1 -

WHEREAS, it was while living and working in Washington, D.C., that she met the love of
her life, Charles "Tif" Bingham; the two were married until the time of Mr. Bingham's passing in
2009; and
WHEREAS, throughout her estimable career, Sandy Dickey demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the sincere respect and admiration of her
colleagues and the citizens of the State of Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and
congratulate Ann Sanders "Sandy" Dickey for her thirty-eight years of exemplary service to
FedEx and the people of Tennessee, congratulate her on the occasion of her retirement, and
extend to her our best wishes for every continued success and happiness in the years to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
